definition.value: A hydroxyflavan that is (2S)-flavan substituted by a hydroxy group at position 4.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group and the heterocyclic ring of FMN-L-serine residue.
An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of uridylyl-L-serine residue; major species at pH 7.3.
An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of uridylyl-L-threonine residue; major species at pH 7.3.
An imidazolyl carboxylic acid that is propanoic acid in which one of the methyl hydrogens is substituted by an imidazol-1-yl group. It is a metabolite of histidine found in human urine and faeces.

A carboxylic ester resulting from the formal condensation of the hydroxy group of aculene D with the carboxylic acid group of L-proline. It is a sesquiterpenoid isolated from the fungus Aspergillus aculeatus.

A carboxylic ester resulting from the formal condensation of the hydroxy group of aculene C with the carboxylic acid group of L-proline. It is a sesquiterpenoid isolated from the fungus Aspergillus aculeatus.
The (S)-enantiomer of flavanone.
An amino acid consisting of carbamic acid having an N-hexyl substituent.

A group of compounds based on the naphthalene ring system where one or more hydrogen atoms have been replaced by chlorine. The generic molecular formula is C10H8-nCln, where n = 1-8. There are 75 possible chlorinated naphthalenes and they are commonly used in the electrical industry and as additives.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from any N(6)-formyl-L-lysine.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from L-methionine sulfone.
Sinapyl acetate in which the configuration of the propenyl double bond is E.
The conjugate base of alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-D-glucose arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
Cinnamyl acetate in which the configuration of the propenyl double bond is E.
A 3-hydroxybutane-1,2,3-tricarboxylic acid which has (2S,3R) configuration.
A benzoate ester obtained by condensation of benzoic acid and butanol. It is used as a perfume ingredient and as a solvent for cellulose ether, a dye carrier for textiles.
A benzoate ester obtained by condensation of benzoic acid and propanol. It has a balsamic odor reminescent of nuts with a sweet, fruity, nut-like taste.
A carboxylic ester obtained by the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-(methylthio)propionic acid with butan-1-ol.
A benzoate ester obtained by condensation of benzoic acid and ethanol. It is a volatile oil component found in ripe kiwifruit, cranberry juice, and palm kernel oil.
This group is attached to proteins in mammalian and E. coli cells (see PDB 1A14 and PMID 7881169).
An acyl-CoA(4-) oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 2-(methylsulfanyl)acetyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A carboxylic ester obtained by the formal condensation of the carboxy group of (methylthio)acetic acid with butan-1-ol.
This group is attached to proteins when expressed in mammalian (PDB 2HR7, 3TYG), insect (PDB 4H53), or fungal (PDB 3A5V) cells.
A tripeptide composed of one L-cysteine and two L-glutamine acid units joined by peptide linkages.
The (2S,3S)-diastereomer of 2-hydroxytridecane-1,2,3-tricarboxylic acid.
A tripeptide composed of L-arginine, L-tryptophan and L-proline joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A sulfuroxoacid with formula H2O2S2.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from alpha-D-glucose-L-threonine.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl-L-threonine.
A secondary alcohol that is  diphenylmethane which carries a hydroxy group at position 1.
This group is attached to proteins when expressed in mammalian (PDB 6OHY) cells.
This group is attached to proteins when expressed in mammalian (PDB 6U7H, 6TYB) and fungal (PDB 6FJE) cells.
A member of the class of  ureas that is urea substituted by an aminomethyl group at the nitrogen atom.
This group is attached to proteins when expressed in mammalian (PDB 6J11)  and fungal (PDB 1SZN) cells.
Attached to proteins that are expressed in insects (PDB 6PZW) and mammals (PDB 6MDT).
A linear amino pentasaccharide comprising the sequence alpha-Neu5Ac, beta-D-Gal, beta-D-GlcNAc, beta-D-Gal and (at the reducing end) beta-D-Glc linked in sequence (2->3), (1->4), (1->3) and (1->4).

A member of the class of fluorenes that is 9-(p-chlorobenzylidene)-9H-fluorene which is substitutec by chlorine at positions 2 and 7, and by a 2-(dibutylamino)-1-hydroxyethyl group at position 4. An antimalarial drug used in combination with artemether for the treatment of multi-drug resistant strains of falciparum malaria.
Attached to proteins that are expressed in fungi (PDB 6Q7J) and mammals (PDB 6QP8).

A branched amino pentasaccharide comprising the linear sequence alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc, to the terminal GlcNAc residue is attached at the 6-position a beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc disaccharide side-branch.
Attached to proteins that are expressed in mammals (PDB 4NCO).
